And stick your hands
out of the window!

559
00:42:25,809 --> 00:42:27,726
Turn off the engine

560
00:42:27,727 --> 00:42:30,996
And stick your hands
out of the window! Now!

561
00:42:47,915 --> 00:42:50,967
Man:
Our relationship with the
swiss has become impossible

562
00:42:50,968 --> 00:42:52,852
Over the past year.

563
00:42:52,853 --> 00:42:54,953
They are discounting
our dollar deposits

564
00:42:54,954 --> 00:42:57,623
By 160 basis points
below par.

565
00:42:57,624 --> 00:43:00,259
They have doubled the cost
of moving our money.

566
00:43:00,260 --> 00:43:03,062
Well, general,
what do you expect?

567
00:43:03,063 --> 00:43:05,064
You've been living in
the jungle long enough

568
00:43:05,065 --> 00:43:06,665
To know that when
the lion kills,

569
00:43:06,666 --> 00:43:08,200
It's the jackal
that profits.

570
00:43:08,201 --> 00:43:09,401
Yes.

571
00:43:10,353 --> 00:43:12,654
The ibbc is
specifically structured

572
00:43:12,655 --> 00:43:15,658
To handle the particular needs
of your type of organization.

573
00:43:15,659 --> 00:43:17,627
Of course we can give you
better rates and terms

574
00:43:17,628 --> 00:43:19,928
Than any other competitors,

575
00:43:19,929 --> 00:43:21,864
But we can offer you
much more:

576
00:43:21,865 --> 00:43:23,666
Weapons,

577
00:43:23,667 --> 00:43:26,669
Intelligence,
logistical support,

578
00:43:26,670 --> 00:43:29,105
Everything that the
revolutionary freedom front

579
00:43:29,106 --> 00:43:31,307
Would need
to revive itself.

580
00:43:31,308 --> 00:43:33,726
But in exchange
for what?

581
00:43:33,727 --> 00:43:37,279
You must understand,
the rff has no money.

582
00:43:40,066 --> 00:43:42,301
Money is not
this institution's

583
00:43:42,302 --> 00:43:45,771
Primary medium of exchange.

584
00:43:45,772 --> 00:43:48,674
[music]

585
00:43:48,675 --> 00:43:51,527
What are you
proposing exactly?

586
00:43:51,528 --> 00:43:52,794
We believe that

587
00:43:52,795 --> 00:43:54,763
With the right kind
of direction and support,

588
00:43:54,764 --> 00:43:57,233
The rff could become
a very influential force

589
00:43:57,234 --> 00:43:58,317
In your country.

590
00:43:58,318 --> 00:44:00,203
Perhaps potent enough

591
00:44:00,204 --> 00:44:04,023
To stage a successful coup
in the coming months.

592
00:44:05,442 --> 00:44:08,010
And if this were possible,

593
00:44:08,011 --> 00:44:10,946
What does your bank
hope to gain from it?

594
00:44:13,283 --> 00:44:15,718
The gratitude and consideration

595
00:44:15,719 --> 00:44:18,754
Of a very influential friend.

596
00:44:19,839 --> 00:44:22,141
Excuse me.

597
00:44:22,142 --> 00:44:26,812
[whispers]
Mr. White and Mr. Ehames
asked me to interrupt.

598
00:44:26,813 --> 00:44:29,298
Would you excuse me, general?
I'll be right back.

599
00:44:42,696 --> 00:44:43,929
What is it?

600
00:44:49,152 --> 00:44:50,736
Approximately
30 minutes ago,

601
00:44:50,737 --> 00:44:52,922
Umberto Calvini
was assassinated,

602
00:44:52,923 --> 00:44:55,458
While giving a speech
at a political rally in milan.

603
00:44:59,012 --> 00:45:01,347
We've been discussing it.

604
00:45:01,348 --> 00:45:02,447
I think
we should wait

605
00:45:02,448 --> 00:45:05,033
Until the authorities
resolve the matter,

606
00:45:05,034 --> 00:45:09,104
And then approach the sons
to revive negotiations.

607
00:45:09,105 --> 00:45:10,606
How long will this take?

608
00:45:10,607 --> 00:45:12,324
I've been assured
the investigation

609
00:45:12,325 --> 00:45:15,327
Will move swiftly, but, uh,

610
00:45:15,328 --> 00:45:18,297
Unexpected fallout
of an event like this

611
00:45:18,298 --> 00:45:19,798
Can always
complicate things.

612
00:45:19,799 --> 00:45:22,400
Man:
We only have 60 days left
to deliver the worms.

613
00:45:22,401 --> 00:45:24,119
There's no time
for complications.

614
00:45:24,120 --> 00:45:27,623
That's a risk you take
with such an ambitious agenda.

615
00:45:27,624 --> 00:45:29,742
White:
I don't foresee any problems.

616
00:45:29,743 --> 00:45:30,943
Had it not been
for their father,

617
00:45:30,944 --> 00:45:33,579
Mario and Enzo Calvini would've
made our deal long ago.

618
00:45:33,580 --> 00:45:35,981
Now there's no reason
for them not to move forward.

619
00:45:37,384 --> 00:45:39,868
An important man
and devoted father

620
00:45:39,869 --> 00:45:41,203
Has just been killed.

621
00:45:43,507 --> 00:45:45,758
I suggest that we send a letter
to Calvini's family,

622
00:45:45,759 --> 00:45:48,194
Extending our heartfelt
prayers and condolences

623
00:45:48,195 --> 00:45:51,296
For their
terrible loss.

624
00:45:51,297 --> 00:45:52,914
Eleanor:
I don't know, but I'm okay.

625
00:45:52,915 --> 00:45:56,101
The doctors
checked me out thoroughly.

626
00:45:56,102 --> 00:45:58,303
Kiss Jake for me, Will you?

627
00:46:05,361 --> 00:46:08,781
Cerutti:
So the shooter was identified
as a member of the red brigade.

628
00:46:08,782 --> 00:46:10,866
Eleanor:
What about the guy in the car?

629
00:46:10,867 --> 00:46:12,585
Cerutti:
The car was stolen.

630
00:46:12,586 --> 00:46:14,620
They were unable to lift
prints, fibers or residue,

631
00:46:14,621 --> 00:46:17,673
Or locate any witnesses who
saw him exiting the vehicle.

632
00:46:17,674 --> 00:46:18,958
So?

633
00:46:18,959 --> 00:46:21,127
The carabinieri are announcing
the red brigade

634
00:46:21,128 --> 00:46:22,878
Was responsible
for the assassination

635
00:46:22,879 --> 00:46:24,496
At the press conference
tonight.

636
00:46:24,497 --> 00:46:27,232
Salinger:
We're not convinced
the red brigade's behind this.

637
00:46:27,233 --> 00:46:30,218
Someone could simply be making
it appear as though they are.

638
00:46:31,204 --> 00:46:33,022
This isn't my case,

639
00:46:33,023 --> 00:46:36,142
And the man in charge of the
investigation is very powerful

640
00:46:36,143 --> 00:46:37,476
And a real bastard.

641
00:46:37,477 --> 00:46:41,379
All we wanna do
is just look around a little.

642
00:46:41,380 --> 00:46:43,315
[music]

643
00:46:56,012 --> 00:46:57,580
[speaking in Italian]

644
00:46:57,581 --> 00:47:00,315
[speaking in Italian]

645
00:47:03,653 --> 00:47:05,921
Antonio.
Alberto.

646
00:47:05,922 --> 00:47:07,756
Just a moment.

647
00:47:07,757 --> 00:47:10,492
[speaking in Italian]

648
00:47:35,018 --> 00:47:38,037
They done the trajectory
analysis yet?

649
00:47:38,038 --> 00:47:40,322
Cerutti said no.

650
00:48:03,230 --> 00:48:05,430
[chatter]

651
00:49:00,220 --> 00:49:01,854
If there was a second shooter,

652
00:49:01,855 --> 00:49:03,672
He could've positioned
himself here.

653
00:49:05,592 --> 00:49:07,275
The stopwatch they found
in the room,

654
00:49:07,276 --> 00:49:09,411
It was set on
a one-minute countdown, yes?

655
00:49:09,412 --> 00:49:11,263
Right. Calvini
was killed

656
00:49:11,264 --> 00:49:13,182
A little over one minute
into his speech.

657
00:49:13,183 --> 00:49:16,335
What if this was
all synchronized?

658
00:49:19,855 --> 00:49:21,657
Okay.

659
00:49:23,459 --> 00:49:25,460
Let's say I'm
the second shooter.

660
00:49:26,529 --> 00:49:28,597
The guy below
doesn't know I'm here,

661
00:49:28,598 --> 00:49:32,467
But I'm positioned
right above his room.

662
00:49:32,468 --> 00:49:37,206
<i>I'm armed with a sauer 200
rifle, just like he is.</i>

663
00:49:37,207 --> 00:49:39,875
I have a stopwatch set
on a one-minute countdown

664
00:49:39,876 --> 00:49:42,494
<i>Which I start when Calvini
begins his speech.</i>

665
00:49:42,495 --> 00:49:44,963
The sniper below has been
instructed to do the same,

666
00:49:44,964 --> 00:49:47,499
Because that's when he's
gonna fire his first bullet.

667
00:49:47,500 --> 00:49:48,801
If he misses,

668
00:49:48,802 --> 00:49:52,588
<i>I'm ready to follow through
with one of my own.</i>

669
00:49:52,589 --> 00:49:55,257
The sniper fires, misses.

670
00:49:55,258 --> 00:49:56,759
<i>Seconds later...</i>

671
00:49:56,760 --> 00:49:57,976
[gunshot]

672
00:49:57,977 --> 00:49:59,878
<i>I take Calvini out
with a headshot.</i>

673
00:50:01,531 --> 00:50:04,282
It's a good theory,
but there's one problem.

674
00:50:04,283 --> 00:50:05,467
Why?

675
00:50:08,605 --> 00:50:11,440
Two shots were fired
from the window,

676
00:50:11,441 --> 00:50:13,275
<i>Two slugs were recovered
from the stage,</i>

677
00:50:13,276 --> 00:50:15,861
And two casings were found
next to the gun.

678
00:50:15,862 --> 00:50:17,680
Ballistics confirming
that the casings

679
00:50:17,681 --> 00:50:19,381
<i>Came from the gun
in the hotel room.</i>

680
00:50:19,382 --> 00:50:22,868
<i>So if the kill shot came from
a second shooter on the roof,</i>

681
00:50:22,869 --> 00:50:25,788
That'd be a total
of three bullets fired.

682
00:50:25,789 --> 00:50:28,073
How do you explain the absence
of the third bullet?

683
00:50:30,093 --> 00:50:32,477
I can't.

684
00:50:47,944 --> 00:50:50,595
[air sucking]

685
00:50:54,701 --> 00:50:56,368
[beeping]

686
00:50:58,788 --> 00:51:00,572
[air blowing]

687
00:51:00,573 --> 00:51:03,993
Salinger:
I think I've seen
this print before.

688
00:51:03,994 --> 00:51:05,444
Eleanor:
Where?

689
00:51:05,445 --> 00:51:07,479
Hanging on the wall
of my office.

690
00:51:08,198 --> 00:51:11,917
[beeping]

691
00:51:18,141 --> 00:51:21,093
[buzzing]

692
00:51:22,612 --> 00:51:24,295
So this was lifted
from the scene

693
00:51:24,296 --> 00:51:26,682
Of the Stefan heuss hit
in brussels last year.

694
00:51:26,683 --> 00:51:28,833
A former
imf executive director.

695
00:51:28,834 --> 00:51:31,019
Has he ever seen a tread
pattern like this before?

696
00:51:31,020 --> 00:51:32,420
[speaking in Italian]

697
00:51:32,421 --> 00:51:35,257
[speaking in Italian]

698
00:51:39,845 --> 00:51:42,347
He believes it came
from a custom shoe

699
00:51:42,348 --> 00:51:43,782
Made for a leg brace.

700
00:51:43,783 --> 00:51:46,118
The braces are typically
made out of steel,

701
00:51:46,119 --> 00:51:48,019
Or alloy,
but the condition of the leg

702
00:51:48,020 --> 00:51:50,388
Would determine the specific
type of device used.

703
00:51:50,389 --> 00:51:52,741
[speaking in Italian]

704
00:51:52,742 --> 00:51:55,227
He says that the prints
are a probable match.

705
00:51:57,480 --> 00:52:00,182
Alberto, can you please
get these over to Alan kovacs

706
00:52:00,183 --> 00:52:01,716
At fbi impressions
right away,

707
00:52:01,717 --> 00:52:04,920
And make sure
he has my contact numbers.

708
00:52:04,921 --> 00:52:07,556
Thanks.

709
00:52:07,557 --> 00:52:09,658
Ella,
if the fbi confirms

710
00:52:09,659 --> 00:52:10,926
That these prints
are a match

711
00:52:10,927 --> 00:52:13,878
It means the bank's
used the same assassin twice.

712
00:52:13,879 --> 00:52:16,031
Which means
if we can get him,

713
00:52:16,032 --> 00:52:16,998
We can get the bank.

714
00:52:16,999 --> 00:52:19,034
[footsteps approaching]

715
00:52:19,035 --> 00:52:20,903
[speaking in Italian]

716
00:52:20,904 --> 00:52:23,789
[speaking in Italian]

717
00:52:23,790 --> 00:52:26,608
[speaking angrily in Italian]

718
00:52:28,378 --> 00:52:29,595
[speaking in Italian]

719
00:52:50,817 --> 00:52:52,468
[scoffs]

720
00:52:52,469 --> 00:52:54,903
What was that?
[loud bang]

721
00:52:58,340 --> 00:53:00,174
<i>That was
capitano barillo,</i>

722
00:53:00,175 --> 00:53:02,260
The man in charge of
the Calvini investigation.

723
00:53:02,261 --> 00:53:03,612
What did he want?

724
00:53:03,613 --> 00:53:05,680
My ass on a platter,

725
00:53:05,681 --> 00:53:08,250
And both of you on
the next flight out of milan.

726
00:53:08,251 --> 00:53:10,502
Well, didn't you tell
him what we just found?

727
00:53:10,503 --> 00:53:12,287
I tried.

728
00:53:12,288 --> 00:53:15,357
Fuck him. He can't
force us to leave.

729
00:53:15,358 --> 00:53:18,076
He has already spoken
to your superiors.

730
00:53:18,077 --> 00:53:21,279
You have both
been ordered home.

731
00:53:21,280 --> 00:53:23,298
Eleanor:
Arnie, you can't just sit there

732
00:53:23,299 --> 00:53:25,266
And lecture me about
protocol and procedure.

733
00:53:25,267 --> 00:53:27,519
You know
what's happening here.

734
00:53:27,520 --> 00:53:29,938
Well, who gives a shit about
jurisdictional provenance?

735
00:53:29,939 --> 00:53:32,190
We just had
a major breakthrough.

736
00:53:32,191 --> 00:53:33,691
[chatter]

737
00:53:33,692 --> 00:53:36,495
Ah, that's great, arnie.
You're a real stand-up guy.

738
00:53:36,496 --> 00:53:38,830
This is
total bullshit.

739
00:53:38,831 --> 00:53:39,982
[sighs]

740
00:53:39,983 --> 00:53:41,516
I wish I could've
been more helpful.

741
00:53:41,517 --> 00:53:43,318
Oh, no, you've been great,
Alberto.

742
00:53:43,319 --> 00:53:45,737
I'm gonna do everything I can
to take the heat off you.

743
00:53:46,956 --> 00:53:49,541
<i>Ciao.
Thanks.</i>

744
00:53:49,542 --> 00:53:52,627
Salinger:
Thanks for everything. Sorry
for all the trouble we caused.

745
00:53:52,628 --> 00:53:54,046
[cerutti speaks in Italian]

746
00:53:54,047 --> 00:53:55,414
[buzzing]

747
00:54:05,091 --> 00:54:06,425
What?

748
00:54:06,426 --> 00:54:09,144
His leg brace would
be made of metal, right?

749
00:54:09,145 --> 00:54:12,364
So?
If he left through an airport,

750
00:54:12,365 --> 00:54:14,900
Security would've made him
show it to them.

751
00:54:14,901 --> 00:54:16,885
[music]

752
00:54:33,803 --> 00:54:35,871
That's definitely him.

753
00:54:35,872 --> 00:54:37,956
He doesn't
look like much.

754
00:54:37,957 --> 00:54:39,708
I think
that's the idea.

755
00:54:39,709 --> 00:54:42,094
Eleanor:
He almost seems to know
where the cameras are.

756
00:54:42,095 --> 00:54:45,163
Look how he always angles his
face out of our line of sight.

757
00:54:45,164 --> 00:54:48,032
Even if you do find him,
that's not enough evidence

758
00:54:48,033 --> 00:54:49,951
To convict the man
without a confession.

759
00:54:49,952 --> 00:54:52,020
If we find him,
prosecution will be irrelevant.

760
00:54:52,021 --> 00:54:53,521
He'll be a marked man.

761
00:54:53,522 --> 00:54:56,024
He can either die for
the bank or flip for us.

762
00:54:56,025 --> 00:54:57,142
[door opens]

763
00:54:57,143 --> 00:54:58,677
I got him.

764
00:54:58,678 --> 00:55:02,064
He is traveling under the name
sherwood. Timothy m.

765
00:55:02,065 --> 00:55:04,283
He boarded flight
alitalia 422,

766
00:55:04,284 --> 00:55:06,218
Departing milan
at 6 p.M. Yesterday,

767
00:55:06,219 --> 00:55:08,987
And arriving in New York
at jfk at 10 p.M.

768
00:55:08,988 --> 00:55:11,323
[music]

769
00:55:11,324 --> 00:55:13,458
What time's the next
flight to New York?

770
00:55:13,459 --> 00:55:15,226
[music]

771
00:55:19,999 --> 00:55:21,933
[horns honking]

772
00:55:53,566 --> 00:55:56,084
Detectives hubbard,
ward, ornelas,

773
00:55:56,085 --> 00:55:57,369
This is agent lou Salinger.

774
00:55:57,370 --> 00:55:59,538
Finally.
Let me take that.

