At the bank's headquarters
in Luxembourg.

1019
01:10:55,100 --> 01:10:58,319
You don't
look well today.

1020
01:10:58,320 --> 01:11:01,155
We all begin better
than we end.

1021
01:11:01,156 --> 01:11:04,408
What would you prefer
your ending to be like?

1022
01:11:04,409 --> 01:11:06,844
Oh, more purposeful,

1023
01:11:06,845 --> 01:11:09,530
And certainly more climactic.

1024
01:11:09,531 --> 01:11:11,699
A finale.

1025
01:11:11,700 --> 01:11:13,601
A finale.

1026
01:11:13,602 --> 01:11:17,622
Circumstances can
always be arranged.

1027
01:11:17,623 --> 01:11:20,290
As much as the thought
appeals to me,

1028
01:11:20,291 --> 01:11:25,046
I'm afraid your consideration
is needed elsewhere.

1029
01:11:25,047 --> 01:11:27,849
What is this?
Salinger.

1030
01:11:27,850 --> 01:11:30,918
The method and manner
is entirely up to you.

1031
01:11:30,919 --> 01:11:33,137
Your principle
would simply like him

1032
01:11:33,138 --> 01:11:36,073
To vanish
without a Trace.

1033
01:11:38,694 --> 01:11:41,879
Any other provisions?
Yes.

1034
01:11:41,880 --> 01:11:43,380
No mistakes.

1035
01:11:45,984 --> 01:11:48,853
I'll follow.

1036
01:11:53,408 --> 01:11:57,127
Where's iggy going?
Following a new lead.

1037
01:12:13,645 --> 01:12:15,496
[music]

1038
01:12:25,440 --> 01:12:27,325
Shit.

1039
01:12:27,326 --> 01:12:28,909
We gotta go.

1040
01:12:30,112 --> 01:12:33,697
N.Y.P.D. Lock your hands
behind your head.

1041
01:12:37,536 --> 01:12:38,836
Do it now.

1042
01:12:38,837 --> 01:12:41,172
They'll never let you
bring me in.

1043
01:12:41,173 --> 01:12:43,390
Do it,
or I'll take you down.

1044
01:12:46,378 --> 01:12:47,845
Cuffs.
On the belt.

1045
01:12:47,846 --> 01:12:49,179
[gunshots with silencer]

1046
01:12:50,599 --> 01:12:52,383
[gunshots with silencer]

1047
01:12:52,384 --> 01:12:53,834
Ah!

1048
01:12:53,835 --> 01:12:55,886
[gurgling]

1049
01:12:55,887 --> 01:12:58,139
Woman:
Oh, my God!

1050
01:12:58,140 --> 01:12:59,607
There's a Guy
right up there.

1051
01:12:59,608 --> 01:13:01,142
[gurgles]

1052
01:13:01,143 --> 01:13:03,460
[people yelling]

1053
01:13:06,982 --> 01:13:08,232
[woman screams]

1054
01:13:08,233 --> 01:13:09,934
[gunshot]

1055
01:13:12,537 --> 01:13:14,271
Ah!

1056
01:13:14,272 --> 01:13:15,539
[crowd screaming]

1057
01:13:20,245 --> 01:13:21,495
[music]

1058
01:13:27,002 --> 01:13:30,254
Where'd he--?
Up there! Up there!

1059
01:13:35,677 --> 01:13:37,211
[panting]

1060
01:13:39,814 --> 01:13:42,683
Get down!

1061
01:13:42,684 --> 01:13:43,950
[screams]

1062
01:13:47,706 --> 01:13:50,107
God! Oh, my God!
It's okay.

1063
01:13:50,108 --> 01:13:52,360
Ah, ah!

1064
01:13:52,361 --> 01:13:53,744
Down there.

1065
01:14:01,620 --> 01:14:03,287
[clicks]

1066
01:14:03,288 --> 01:14:06,090
Shit.

1067
01:14:06,091 --> 01:14:07,591
[woman sobs]

1068
01:14:16,401 --> 01:14:17,367
[shooting]

1069
01:14:20,856 --> 01:14:21,839
[gunshots]

1070
01:14:25,027 --> 01:14:26,694
Drop the gun.

1071
01:14:26,695 --> 01:14:27,711
[gun cocks]

1072
01:14:27,712 --> 01:14:29,730
If I drop the gun,
we'll both die.

1073
01:14:29,731 --> 01:14:31,649
I said, drop the gun!

1074
01:14:31,650 --> 01:14:33,951
They're here for me
but they'll kill you too.

1075
01:14:33,952 --> 01:14:35,902
Now help me
get this off.

1076
01:14:37,239 --> 01:14:38,489
I can't breathe.

1077
01:14:46,548 --> 01:14:48,699
[screams and glass shattering]

1078
01:15:01,145 --> 01:15:03,297
Stairs.

1079
01:15:11,189 --> 01:15:12,323
[groans]

1080
01:15:12,324 --> 01:15:13,457
[shooting]

1081
01:15:13,458 --> 01:15:15,058
[groans]

1082
01:15:15,059 --> 01:15:17,260
Fuck.
You okay?

1083
01:15:18,997 --> 01:15:20,080
[shouting]

1084
01:15:20,081 --> 01:15:21,682
The ramp is
the only way out.

1085
01:15:24,836 --> 01:15:26,170
[exhales]

1086
01:15:26,171 --> 01:15:27,721
[gunshots]

1087
01:15:27,722 --> 01:15:30,040
[music]

1088
01:15:30,041 --> 01:15:32,576
[gun cocks]

1089
01:15:45,474 --> 01:15:47,240
[sobbing]

1090
01:16:06,878 --> 01:16:08,712
[squeaking]

1091
01:16:08,713 --> 01:16:10,881
[groans]

1092
01:16:10,882 --> 01:16:13,050
[gunshot]

1093
01:16:13,051 --> 01:16:15,769
[music]

1094
01:16:17,572 --> 01:16:19,640
[groaning]

1095
01:16:19,641 --> 01:16:20,891
[gunshots]

1096
01:16:26,765 --> 01:16:27,914
[groaning]

1097
01:16:35,857 --> 01:16:37,391
[groans and screams]

1098
01:16:40,111 --> 01:16:41,495
[woman screaming]

1099
01:16:41,496 --> 01:16:43,463
[gunshots]

1100
01:17:21,403 --> 01:17:23,153
[yells]

1101
01:17:31,846 --> 01:17:33,012
[groans]

1102
01:17:36,734 --> 01:17:38,953
Hey.

1103
01:17:40,021 --> 01:17:42,272
Don't you fucking dare.

1104
01:17:42,273 --> 01:17:44,124
[gunshots]

1105
01:17:55,370 --> 01:17:57,120
[groans]

1106
01:18:07,699 --> 01:18:09,850
[metal clanging]

1107
01:18:15,423 --> 01:18:17,291
[clang]

1108
01:18:17,292 --> 01:18:18,926
[woman screaming]

1109
01:18:18,927 --> 01:18:21,345
[shattering]

1110
01:18:35,694 --> 01:18:38,161
<i>Mechanical voice:
I'm calling from the dark side.</i>

1111
01:18:38,162 --> 01:18:39,680
Sorry. Sorry.

1112
01:18:39,681 --> 01:18:42,115
<i>I'm calling from the--
sorry.</i>

1113
01:18:59,867 --> 01:19:02,836
[music]

1114
01:19:02,837 --> 01:19:04,772
[groans quietly]

1115
01:19:08,376 --> 01:19:10,277
[sirens wailing]

1116
01:19:19,904 --> 01:19:21,138
Get back.

1117
01:19:25,393 --> 01:19:26,826
[tires squealing]

1118
01:19:36,538 --> 01:19:38,388
[panting]

1119
01:19:41,392 --> 01:19:43,193
I told you.

1120
01:19:45,062 --> 01:19:47,664
What? You told me what?

1121
01:19:48,983 --> 01:19:51,885
They'd never let you
bring me in.

1122
01:20:09,254 --> 01:20:12,422
[music]

1123
01:20:12,423 --> 01:20:13,557
F--

1124
01:20:17,912 --> 01:20:19,296
Fuck, fuck, fuck.

1125
01:20:19,297 --> 01:20:21,832
[sirens continue wailing]

1126
01:20:29,224 --> 01:20:31,625
<i>Man [over loudspeaker]:
Move away from the building.</i>

1127
01:20:31,626 --> 01:20:35,462
<i>Can everybody please
move away from the building?</i>

1128
01:20:46,324 --> 01:20:48,124
<i>[indistinct speaking
over radio]</i>

1129
01:20:53,998 --> 01:20:56,266
They know you're coming.
We gotta hurry.

1130
01:20:56,267 --> 01:20:57,367
Where'd they
find him?

1131
01:20:57,368 --> 01:20:59,837
Sitting on a bench
near the reservoir.

1132
01:20:59,838 --> 01:21:01,371
Has he said
anything yet?

1133
01:21:01,372 --> 01:21:03,707
Nothing.
He's pretty shaken up.

1134
01:21:03,708 --> 01:21:04,757
Who else
knows he's here?

1135
01:21:04,758 --> 01:21:07,544
Everyone.
Nothing I could do.

1136
01:21:07,545 --> 01:21:09,963
Heavies from the bureau
and Justice are on their way.

1137
01:21:09,964 --> 01:21:12,031
<i>Man [on TV]:
--With an unidentified
third man.</i>

1138
01:21:12,032 --> 01:21:13,383
How long do I have?

1139
01:21:13,384 --> 01:21:14,951
Five,
10 minutes, Max.

1140
01:21:14,952 --> 01:21:17,971
<i>--Wanted for questioning
in an ongoing investigation.</i>

1141
01:21:17,972 --> 01:21:20,674
<i>Now, a guggenheim employee
tells me</i>

1142
01:21:20,675 --> 01:21:22,375
<i>That while they were
in the museum--</i>

1143
01:21:22,376 --> 01:21:23,893
[door closes]

1144
01:21:59,280 --> 01:22:02,248
This isn't over.

1145
01:22:04,519 --> 01:22:07,554
[music]

1146
01:22:19,701 --> 01:22:21,535
Are you sure about this?

1147
01:22:21,536 --> 01:22:23,219
[sirens wailing]

1148
01:22:27,124 --> 01:22:28,375
Just read it.

1149
01:22:41,556 --> 01:22:43,524
[horn honks]

1150
01:22:43,525 --> 01:22:45,925
They recognize you?
Don't think so.

1151
01:22:45,926 --> 01:22:47,694
[horn honks]

1152
01:22:49,063 --> 01:22:50,113
[horns honking]

1153
01:22:50,114 --> 01:22:52,182
Man:
Back it up!

1154
01:22:52,183 --> 01:22:53,917
[tires squealing]

1155
01:22:57,238 --> 01:22:58,838
[music]

1156
01:23:33,691 --> 01:23:36,026
<i>Woman [on TV]: Came crashing--
how you doing, al?</i>

1157
01:23:36,027 --> 01:23:37,945
<i>[door closes]
there was glass everywhere.</i>

1158
01:23:37,946 --> 01:23:39,696
As compared to what?

1159
01:23:39,697 --> 01:23:41,431
<i>And just on the ground.</i>

1160
01:23:41,432 --> 01:23:44,501
<i>Man [on TV]:
When you heard all of this
commotion, did you think--?</i>

1161
01:23:44,502 --> 01:23:46,370
Anything you need, Ellie,
just let me know.

1162
01:23:46,371 --> 01:23:47,437
Thanks.

1163
01:23:47,438 --> 01:23:49,139
<i>Woman [on TV]:
I just heard gunshots.</i>

1164
01:23:49,140 --> 01:23:51,408
<i>And people were hit
and screaming,</i>

1165
01:23:51,409 --> 01:23:53,443
<i>And people just started
running out the door,</i>

1166
01:23:53,444 --> 01:23:55,428
<i>And I didn't know
what was going on.</i>

1167
01:23:55,429 --> 01:23:56,763
You okay?

1168
01:23:56,764 --> 01:23:58,798
Yeah.

1169
01:24:00,668 --> 01:24:03,169
You flip this guy.

1170
01:24:03,170 --> 01:24:06,607
You make sure my partner
wasn't killed for nothing.

1171
01:24:06,608 --> 01:24:10,260
<i>Woman [on TV]:
I know that-- I think random
people were going down and--</i>

1172
01:24:10,261 --> 01:24:12,011
<i>I mean, there was
police running up</i>

1173
01:24:12,012 --> 01:24:15,181
<i>As other people
were going down.</i>

1174
01:24:22,606 --> 01:24:24,791
[music]

1175
01:24:27,378 --> 01:24:29,178
You ready for this?

1176
01:24:54,772 --> 01:24:56,139
[door closes]

1177
01:25:05,533 --> 01:25:08,335
Good evening,
colonel wexler.

1178
01:25:09,870 --> 01:25:13,272
I'm agent
Louis Salinger.

1179
01:25:13,273 --> 01:25:16,108
I know who you are.

1180
01:25:17,462 --> 01:25:19,262
Of course you do.

1181
01:25:21,532 --> 01:25:24,000
I was at the guggenheim
this afternoon.

1182
01:25:26,137 --> 01:25:29,356
<i>Salinger [over speaker]:
The assassin you met with...</i>

1183
01:25:29,357 --> 01:25:31,808
<i>I know you were his handler.</i>

1184
01:25:31,809 --> 01:25:33,694
And I know that you arranged
for him to be killed

1185
01:25:33,695 --> 01:25:34,828
At the behest of the bank,

1186
01:25:34,829 --> 01:25:37,497
Because I was obviously
getting too close.

1187
01:25:40,785 --> 01:25:43,437
But if a hit team at the
guggenheim is what happens

1188
01:25:43,438 --> 01:25:46,273
Because I was
getting too close to him...

1189
01:25:48,709 --> 01:25:50,277
What do you think
the bank's gonna do

1190
01:25:50,278 --> 01:25:52,045
When it realizes
how close I am to you?

1191
01:25:52,046 --> 01:25:57,751
Death comes for us all,
agent Salinger.

1192
01:25:57,752 --> 01:26:00,319
Yeah, but based on everything
I've read about you,

1193
01:26:00,320 --> 01:26:02,188
You seem like the kind of man

1194
01:26:02,189 --> 01:26:05,391
Who aspired to die
for something more than this.

1195
01:26:06,844 --> 01:26:11,715
Well, this is the difference
between truth and fiction.

1196
01:26:12,850 --> 01:26:15,135
Fiction has to make sense.

1197
01:26:17,772 --> 01:26:19,922
I'm confused, colonel.

1198
01:26:23,027 --> 01:26:26,028
Why would a tried
and true communist,

1199
01:26:26,029 --> 01:26:28,782
A hardliner that spent
30 years in the stasi

1200
01:26:28,783 --> 01:26:31,201
Fighting against the evils
of capitalism...

1201
01:26:31,202 --> 01:26:32,785
Why would this man waste

1202
01:26:32,786 --> 01:26:34,604
His final days
working for an institution

1203
01:26:34,605 --> 01:26:38,641
That was the very embodiment
of everything he once despised?

1204
01:26:41,094 --> 01:26:44,314
Salinger:
You dedicated your life
to the communist ideal.

1205
01:26:46,400 --> 01:26:49,803
You sacrificed everything
for the good of the party.

1206
01:26:51,372 --> 01:26:53,006
For what?

1207
01:26:56,326 --> 01:26:59,795
You lost your wife
to betrayal.

1208
01:26:59,796 --> 01:27:02,198
Your daughter to suicide.

1209
01:27:03,501 --> 01:27:04,800
And when the wall fell,

1210
01:27:04,801 --> 01:27:07,070
Your whole life
fell apart with it.

1211
01:27:07,071 --> 01:27:09,823
You know nothing about me.

1212
01:27:09,824 --> 01:27:14,110
I was lost long
before the wall fell.

1213
01:27:14,111 --> 01:27:19,132
I was once destined to become
a man much like yourself.

1214
01:27:19,133 --> 01:27:21,334
True-hearted,

1215
01:27:21,335 --> 01:27:23,436
Determined,

1216
01:27:23,437 --> 01:27:26,406
Full of purpose.

1217
01:27:26,407 --> 01:27:28,841
But, uh,

1218
01:27:28,842 --> 01:27:31,777
Character is easier kept
than recovered.

1219
01:27:33,097 --> 01:27:37,400
We cannot control
the things life does to us.

1220
01:27:37,401 --> 01:27:40,136
They are done
before you know it,

1221
01:27:40,137 --> 01:27:42,655
And once they are done,

1222
01:27:42,656 --> 01:27:45,325
They make you do other things,

1223
01:27:45,326 --> 01:27:49,696
Until at last
everything comes between you

1224
01:27:49,697 --> 01:27:52,715
And the man you wanted to be.

1225
01:27:54,151 --> 01:27:55,818
No.

1226
01:27:57,521 --> 01:28:00,990
We all have choices in life.
You made yours.

1227
01:28:07,982 --> 01:28:10,283
Sometimes a man
can meet his destiny

1228
01:28:10,284 --> 01:28:12,085
On the road
he took to avoid it.

1229
01:28:15,473 --> 01:28:18,157
Skarssen and that bank need
to answer for what they've done.

1230
01:28:18,158 --> 01:28:20,293
They have to be
brought to Justice.

1231
01:28:20,294 --> 01:28:22,612
You can help me do that.

1232
01:28:22,613 --> 01:28:25,214
Justice

1233
01:28:25,215 --> 01:28:27,484
Is not possible.

1234
01:28:27,485 --> 01:28:29,736
Why not?

1235
01:28:29,737 --> 01:28:32,438
Because, agent Salinger,

1236
01:28:32,439 --> 01:28:36,826
Your idea of Justice
is an illusion.

1237
01:28:36,827 --> 01:28:38,928
<i>[over speaker]
don't you understand
the very system</i>

1238
01:28:38,929 --> 01:28:40,263
<i>That you serve
and protect</i>

1239
01:28:40,264 --> 01:28:41,831
<i>Will never allow
anything to happen</i>

1240
01:28:41,832 --> 01:28:43,917
<i>To Skarssen
or the bank?</i>

1241
01:28:43,918 --> 01:28:46,002
Wexler:
On the contrary.

1242
01:28:46,003 --> 01:28:50,307
The system guarantees
the ibbc's safety,

1243
01:28:50,308 --> 01:28:54,144
Because everyone is involved.

1244
01:28:54,145 --> 01:28:56,779
What do you mean,
"everyone"?

1245
01:28:59,200 --> 01:29:01,234
Hezbollah.

1246
01:29:01,235 --> 01:29:03,737
Cia.

1247
01:29:03,738 --> 01:29:05,689
The columbian drug cartels.

1248
01:29:05,690 --> 01:29:08,191
Russian organized crime.

1249
01:29:08,192 --> 01:29:12,078
<i>[over speaker]
governments of iran, germany,
china, your government.</i>

1250
01:29:12,079 --> 01:29:15,282
Every multinational
corporation, every one.

1251
01:29:15,283 --> 01:29:19,869
They all need
banks like the ibbc

1252
01:29:19,870 --> 01:29:21,671
So that they can operate

1253
01:29:21,672 --> 01:29:25,225
Within the black
and gray latitudes.

1254
01:29:25,226 --> 01:29:27,376
And this is why
your investigative efforts

1255
01:29:27,377 --> 01:29:31,181
Have either been ignored
or undermined,

1256
01:29:31,182 --> 01:29:34,634
And why you and I
will be quietly disposed of

1257
01:29:34,635 --> 01:29:37,837
Before any case
against the bank

1258
01:29:37,838 --> 01:29:40,573
Ever reaches a court of law.

1259
01:29:46,229 --> 01:29:48,865
<i>[over speaker]
so, what are we all
supposed to do?</i>

1260
01:29:51,818 --> 01:29:54,254
We just supposed
to give up,

1261
01:29:54,255 --> 01:29:57,857
And accept that this
is the way of the world?

1262
01:30:01,412 --> 01:30:03,763
I'm not gonna do that.

1263
01:30:04,865 --> 01:30:08,201
I still believe--
I know--

1264
01:30:08,202 --> 01:30:12,238
That there has to be a way
to bring down this bank,

1265
01:30:12,239 --> 01:30:14,741
And you are
gonna help me.

1266
01:30:21,782 --> 01:30:23,916
You understand...

1267
01:30:25,319 --> 01:30:29,689
If you really want
to stop the ibbc,

1268
01:30:29,690 --> 01:30:31,324
You won't be able
to do it

1269
01:30:31,325 --> 01:30:35,328
Within the boundaries
of your system of Justice.

1270
01:30:35,329 --> 01:30:38,415
You will have to go outside.

1271
01:30:38,416 --> 01:30:40,500
Once you do...

1272
01:30:41,935 --> 01:30:45,738
There will always be
collateral damage.

1273
01:30:50,044 --> 01:30:52,979
<i>[over speaker]
yes.</i>

1274
01:30:52,980 --> 01:30:56,916
<i>Should you sacrifice your own
ideals for the greater good?</i>

1275
